01:19:22.830 --> 01:19:26.670
Yeah, but wasn't Percy voted guitarist of the year by Kerrang Rock Monthly?

01:19:26.670 --> 01:19:30.170
Look, look, I love the whole bit with the fuzzy guitar, but he's overrated, love, right?

01:19:30.170 --> 01:19:35.230
We're out the torrents of abuse, love fist would be over, and the new contract reflects that.

01:19:35.230 --> 01:19:37.870
As an artist, it's

00:00:00.000 --> 00:02:570
really important that I make a lot of money.

00:02:570 --> 00:04:350
Right, man.

00:04:350 --> 00:06:800
You need to keep you in a fridge in there, diamonds and that, hey?

00:06:800 --> 00:10:480
Yeah, right on.
Keith, Roger, what a trip.

00:10:480 --> 00:12:970
Yeah, shut up, you silly tot.

00:13:350 --> 00:14:920
Ah, let's take a caller.

00:14:920 --> 00:16:120
Hello.

00:16:120 --> 00:18:970
Yeah, I'm on the line with Love Fist.

00:18:970 --> 00:19.660
Hi.

00:19:660 --> 00:21.290
Yo, this is Wayne, man.

00:22:930 --> 00:24.930
Hey guys, I'm on the phone with Love Fist.

01:19:54.930 --> 01:19:56.020
Hold on a second.

01:19:56.020 --> 01:19:57.630
Hey, what's up, Jess?

01:19:57.630 --> 01:20:00.360
I'm a huge fan.
I go to all your concerts.

01:20:00.360 --> 01:20:02.460
I get crazy.
I wear my Love Fist t-shirt every day.

01:20:02.460 --> 01:20:05.460
Even when I'm with my old lady.

01:20:05.460 --> 01:20:09.450
Hey, I heard there's subliminal messages in your video.
Is that true?

01:20:09.790 --> 01:20:12.030
Listen, seriously, the big hair,

01:20:12.030 --> 01:20:15.850
the limousines, the gutters, the partying, the clubs, the hotel suites,

01:20:15.850 --> 01:20:19.250
another TV smashed into a thousand pieces, right?

01:20:19.250 --> 01:20:22.820
After my unfortunate incident in Cleveland, I told the press,

01:20:22.820 --> 01:20:25.490
I don't like Mondays.
This livens up the day.

01:20:25.490 --> 01:20:29.700
If you're asking me if we was using backmasking, the music is reversible,

01:20:29.700 --> 01:20:32.430
but time is not.

01:20:32.430 --> 01:20:36.660
Do you want me to say, congratulations, you have just discovered the secret message.

01:20:36.660 --> 01:20:39.630
Dreams are made to be broken.

01:20:39.630 --> 01:20:43.090
Like so many broken dreams, I want to pick up the pieces together.

01:20:44.160 --> 01:20:46.100
God, I am so creative, love.

01:20:48.200 --> 01:20:50.610
Oh, wow, I think I've just wrote a song.

01:20:50.610 --> 01:20:53.260
Maybe I'll write a song about you, hey?

01:20:53.820 --> 01:20:57.870
But anyway, like I say, that stuff it doesn't matter for not for me.

01:20:57.870 --> 01:21:00.740
I'm a spiritual person on a journey, right?

01:21:00.740 --> 01:21:03.500
And nothing will stand in my way, you know?

01:21:03.500 --> 01:21:05.320
Boy, do I.

01:21:05.320 --> 01:21:07.660
On the track, Satan's.

01:21:00.000 --> 01:21:03.000
you sang about how a broken heart can be.
01:21:03.000 --> 01:21:06.520
broken heart can never be mended, just broken again.
01:21:06.520 --> 01:21:10.080
I know, really powerful stuff, emotional.
01:21:10.080 --> 01:21:15.060
I think that song says everything that needs to be said about love, man.
01:21:15.060 --> 01:21:20.220
When you belong to the night, it's best to take advantage of it.
01:21:20.220 --> 01:21:24.870
And what takes you up will take you down, man.
01:21:24.870 --> 01:21:29.220
If everyone remembered that, the world would be okay.
01:21:29.220 --> 01:21:31.140
Thanks, love.
01:21:31.140 --> 01:21:33.600
You are a real smart cookie.
01:21:33.600 --> 01:21:35.910
Thanks, Charles.
01:21:35.910 --> 01:21:43.530
Now, do you think it's important that, well, I mean, you're a great looking guy, even though your girlfriend is a cheap tramp.
01:21:43.530 --> 01:21:50.010
But do you think it's important that rock and roll bands look good or is it about the music?
01:21:50.010 --> 01:21:53.520
Like I said, I'm a creature with two faces, babe, you know.
01:21:53.520 --> 01:21:57.930
An angel and a devil, and that means it's really important to look good.
01:21:57.930 --> 01:22:02.880
Music cannot stand on its own, you need to look good singing it.
01:22:02.880 --> 01:22:08.280
I'm tired of people saying all we care about is partying and that we can't play.
01:22:08.280 --> 01:22:12.390
If we couldn't play, people wouldn't come to our concerts.
01:22:12.390 --> 01:22:17.730
We're not going away, and if we do, it won't be on purpose.
01:22:17.730 --> 01:22:19.380
Where are we, dear Creek?
01:22:19.380 --> 01:22:24.360
We're on the radio, love, stop dragging me down.
01:22:24.360 --> 01:22:28.860
I told you, if you ride the whirlwind, don't be surprised when the dawn breaks.
01:22:28.860 --> 01:22:30.240
Anyway, where were we?
01:22:30.240 --> 01:22:34.350
Oh, she's really getting on my nerves.
01:22:34.350 --> 01:22:37.200
Why are you waving your hands at me?
01:22:37.200 --> 01:22:39.210
Oh, I'm supposed to go to commercial.
01:22:39.210 --> 01:22:41.040
I'll be right back.
01:22:41.040 --> 01:22:42.170
Here we go.
01:22:42.170 --> 01:22:44.880
Howdy, welcome to Farewell Ranch.
01:22:44.880 --> 01:22:51.240
They say the golden years are the best years of your life, but for many seniors, they just stink up the house and make the grandkids feel uncomfortable with unbounding affection.
01:22:51.240 --> 01:22:55.800
Now, your old people can be earning their keep.

01:22:30.000 --> 01:22:41.050
to money and enjoying the final years of Farewell Ranch.
It's a working farm, cattle ranch and crematorium where the cowboys are all over 75.
They'll enjoy rodeos, working in the fields and tending all the final resting places of their new friends on Sunshine Hill.

01:22:41.050 --> 01:22:48.330
Farewell Ranch rocks your loved ones from sun up to sun down, and when your loved one passes away, we'll send you a presentation package, VHS with the spurs and boots they were wearing as they went on to a better world.

01:22:48.330 --> 01:22:51.660
Our residents sure love it here.
Right Norm?
This is WW2.

01:22:51.660 --> 01:22:55.930
Farewell Ranch, the only way to ride into the sunset.

01:22:57.090 --> 01:23:00.390
That's the sound I love.
Starts my morning, you make my night.

01:23:00.390 --> 01:23:05.210
Giggle cream with everything, you make life glow.
Getting fat and happy, laughing and getting fried.

01:23:05.210 --> 01:23:08.180
Mix giggle cream, get both things and what's more fun than that?

01:23:10.180 --> 01:23:11.830
That's the sound I love.

01:23:11.830 --> 01:23:14.410
Giggle cream, it makes dessert funny.

01:23:15.500 --> 01:23:20.180
Asian pajamas, Chinese bandana, something missing?
Complete the look.

01:23:20.180 --> 01:23:25.500
With a throwing star, Kendo sticks or nunchucks at Vice City's one stop shop for the silent fashion assassin.

01:23:25.500 --> 01:23:27.810
Wow, you look like a psycho.

01:23:27.810 --> 01:23:29.970
Complete the look.

01:23:31.390 --> 01:23:32.970
Hi, I'm Amy.

01:24:00.000 --> 01:24:02.790
man, you're on Page chat.
01:24:02.790 --> 01:24:06.040
Jazz, you were telling me about the music?
01:24:06.360 --> 01:24:13.100
Ah, yeah. You know, we wear these costumes to appeal to the working man, because after you spend the day working in a steel mill,
01:24:13.100 --> 01:24:20.060
you want to wear tight leather clothes and play your guitar. That's what we're about.
01:24:20.060 --> 01:24:25.400
The recent album was a musical trip through hell, and I think it shows.
01:24:25.690 --> 01:24:27.330
Oh, yeah, it does.
01:24:27.750 --> 01:24:32.180
I mean, I saw Satan.
01:24:32.180 --> 01:24:35.990
He didn't like what he saw in me.
01:24:35.990 --> 01:24:40.330
He saw darkness, but also a gentle side.
01:24:40.330 --> 01:24:41.930
Ask man.
01:24:42.390 --> 01:24:47.880
I can find treasure in the dark, and it's that, um, it's that, uh, uh, what's the word?
01:24:48.130 --> 01:24:48.650
Thing?
01:24:48.970 --> 01:24:54.110
Yeah, that's the thing that typifies me as an artist, heart and soul, head and trousers, everything.
01:24:54.110 --> 01:25:02.160
That's what you get at one of my shows. Jess Torrent and Love First will really show you, you know, we take the soul into darkness, bring your lighters.
01:25:02.160 --> 01:25:05.490
You know, I invented that.
01:25:05.490 --> 01:25:11.280
I've about had it with wankers ripping off my vibe.
01:25:11.280 --> 01:25:15.950
I wore women's clothing first.
01:25:15.950 --> 01:25:21.150
Why? Because it tells you about light and darkness, like the moon.
01:25:21.690 --> 01:25:25.690
But seriously, love, you've got great eyes, really.
01:25:26.090 --> 01:25:32.230
Oh, thanks, Jazz.
01:25:32.230 --> 01:25:37.750
I've always thought your music really lets people see into your soul.
01:25:38.020 --> 01:25:42.480
Right, into great big pools of pain like me.
01:25:42.480 --> 01:25:45.570
Dangerous bastard.
01:25:45.570 --> 01:25:51.060
You see, babe, I've had my heart broken and I am still a man.
01:25:51.060 --> 01:25:57.310
I'm working on a song right now called Fallen Stars on shattered dreams in the rain.
01:25:57.310 --> 01:26:00.060
It's about being a

01:25:30.000 --> 01:25:32.840
able to communicate through music.
01:25:33.260 --> 01:25:36.080
in a wind tunnel.
01:25:36.080 --> 01:25:40.620
That's why there's a huge snake painted on my jacket.
01:25:40.620 --> 01:25:45.420
The snake symbolizes kind of a subconscious power force.
01:25:45.910 --> 01:25:49.060
Because life is pain, babe.
01:25:49.460 --> 01:25:52.680
And without music, I'd be lost.
01:25:52.980 --> 01:25:56.690
This new album, it's our most mature work yet.
01:25:56.970 --> 01:26:01.360
I am brilliant on it because I sing from the heart.
01:26:01.680 --> 01:26:03.730
About heartbreak?
01:26:03.980 --> 01:26:06.010
Babe, babe, babe, don't go there, please.
01:26:06.530 --> 01:26:10.010
You do your show a favor, take it easy.
01:26:10.230 --> 01:26:14.130
My people spoke to your people about us and seriously, I appreciate the offer.
01:26:14.590 --> 01:26:18.450
And look, I would shag you, but you have to understand it's too soon.
01:26:18.930 --> 01:26:20.960
Because Sherry left you, right?
01:26:21.270 --> 01:26:25.890
Babe, babe, my people spoke about this to your people.
01:26:25.890 --> 01:26:28.420
I said, do not mention Sherry.
01:26:29.030 --> 01:26:32.450
It's like sticking needles in my soul, voodoo.
01:26:33.150 --> 01:26:35.210
Who are you?
01:26:35.710 --> 01:26:39.360
Are you my personal devil that you could do this to me?
01:26:39.360 --> 01:26:42.320
The pain is too much.
01:26:42.580 --> 01:26:46.430
I have hair in my face to hide my soul.
01:26:46.880 --> 01:26:50.300
Sherry had to go because she wanted to be a marine.
01:26:50.680 --> 01:26:53.870
We couldn't be together.
01:26:53.870 --> 01:26:55.940
Seriously, don't go there.
01:26:56.400 --> 01:26:59.750
This is so sad.
01:27:00.070 --> 01:27:02.440
Do you want a tissue out there?
01:27:02.440 --> 01:27:04.220
Oh, Jess, I'm so sorry.
01:27:04.820 --> 01:27:09.570
Seriously, love, if you listen to the song Dragon Eyes, it says everything that needs to be said about her.
01:27:10.090 --> 01:27:13.240
You can't help me.
01:27:13.240 --> 01:27:17.300
It's raw, like a chicken's head, you know?
01:27:17.690 --> 01:27:21.470
The pain grips you and makes you think about everything.
01:27:21.860 --> 01:27:25.840
It's the longest night of all, December of the soul.
01:27:26.450 --> 01:27:31.900
Jess, this has been the best interview of my life.

01:27:00.000 --> 01:27:02.160
Thanks so much for coming on.
01:27:02.160 --> 01:27:07.260
For all you Love Fist fans out there, it's time for a contest.
01:27:07.680 --> 01:27:11.870
That's right, ladies and gents, you're listening to me, Jazz Torrent on K Chat,
01:27:11.870 --> 01:27:15.150
being interviewed by by.
01:27:15.150 --> 01:27:17.120
It's Amy.
01:27:17.120 --> 01:27:19.770
Oh God, you forgot my name?
01:27:19.770 --> 01:27:21.480
Yeah, yeah, whatever.
01:27:21.480 --> 01:27:26.610
Citizens of Vice City, now you've got the opportunity to win a part of me, my signature, ink.
01:27:26.610 --> 01:27:33.120
I only give away parts of myself to people who have bought all our records, so you've got to answer this, on which album did Beast Fist appear?
01:27:33.590 --> 01:27:42.090
Was it A, Dogs on Heat, B, Fat Chicks all day all night, or C, Devil's Own Band?
01:27:42.090 --> 01:27:48.600
For the chance to win tons of Love Fist prizes, just answer the question.
01:27:48.600 --> 01:27:54.150
All you need to do is write the answer on a postcard and send it into the station.
01:27:54.150 --> 01:27:59.010
Jazz, before you go, will you please play us a song acoustic?
00:00:59.380 --> 01:01:150
Piss off, acoustic songs are for sissies.
01:28:01.150 --> 01:28:04.710
Babe, seriously, do not cramp my style.
01:28:04.710 --> 01:28:08.340
Look, I've got to save up the love for the big show.
01:28:08.340 --> 01:28:12.510
Babe, I love you, I really do, friends for life.
01:28:12.510 --> 01:28:15.750
Dance into the fire and all that.
01:28:15.750 --> 01:28:19.560
Always good to meet a fan.
01:28:19.560 --> 01:28:21.780
You look after man for us, will you?
01:28:21.780 --> 01:28:23.910
Oh, I lost my lighter again.
01:28:24.290 --> 01:28:25.640
Love Fist.
01:28:26.170 --> 01:28:33.370
That was the dreamy Jazz Torrent of Love Fist, who are appearing this week in Vice City as part of their world tour.
01:28:33.370 --> 01:28:38.900
Bring your lighters and a spare pair of panties.
01:28:38.900 --> 01:28:40.790
I know I will.
01:28:40.790 --> 01:28:45.050
We'll be right back on K Chat after these messages.
01:28:45.050 --> 01:28:45.830
Thanks.
01:28:46.385 --> 01:28:49.845
What makes a real American?
01:28:49.845 --> 01:28:51.445
A cowboy?

01:28:30.000 --> 01:28:38.030
hats, enjoying a fine T-bone steak, going to a baseball game, shooting a gun.
01:28:38.030 --> 01:28:43.140
Maybe it's the freedom to go into a poor country and tell them how to do things.
01:28:43.140 --> 01:28:47.930
Hey, those are all great qualities, but one thing that makes a true patriot is the ability to choose an American car.
01:28:47.930 --> 01:28:54.820
When you buy an import, you take a hot meal off a hard working American's table.
01:28:55.670 --> 01:28:58.880
There, there, this poor girl is going to starve to death.
01:28:58.880 --> 01:29:04.140
Just because you bought a cheaper, more efficient, mybatsu.
01:29:04.140 --> 01:29:10.760
Without gross symbols of excess, what will Americans have to look up to?
01:29:10.760 --> 01:29:15.310
Our great industries are threatened, cars, pornography, armaments.
01:29:15.310 --> 01:29:20.300
And they need your help, so the next time you buy a car, a piece of adult literature, or a missile defense system.
01:29:20.300 --> 01:29:24.970
Make sure you do the American thing.
01:29:26.720 --> 01:29:29.490
Old Max, we go everywhere together, right, boy?
01:29:29.490 --> 01:29:34.370
At Pet Stuffers, we know there's nothing like a relationship between a man and his dog.
01:29:34.370 --> 01:29:37.320
Sometimes you just can't let go.
01:29:37.320 --> 01:29:39.950
Max, you didn't eat your food.
01:29:39.950 --> 01:29:43.660
That's the second week in a row.
01:29:43.660 --> 01:29:45.200
Max?
01:29:45.200 --> 01:29:51.090
When the unspeakable happens, just put your four-legged friend in the refrigerator or freezer.
01:29:51.090 --> 01:29:55.590
Then call Pet Stuffers, we'll be there within a week to pick him up.
01:29:55.590 --> 01:30:00.600
And in less than a month, he'll be back as good as new, through an ancient Egyptian miracle process called taxidermy.
01:30:00.600 --> 01:30:04.990
You and your best friend will always be together.
01:30:04.990 --> 01:30:07.410
Yeah, that's a good dog.

01:30:00.000 --> 01:30:03.590
Pet Stuffers, when you just can't let go.
01:30:03.590 --> 01:30:07.590
And coming soon, Grandparents Forever.
01:30:07.590 --> 01:30:13.090
The key to feeling great is looking great, and the way to look great is to have great hair.
01:30:13.090 --> 01:30:14.090
That's great.
01:30:14.090 --> 01:30:21.240
With Sissy Spritz, when you're clubbing or sticking your head out of a stretch limo sunroof, you want to know your hair is performing to the limit.
01:30:21.240 --> 01:30:26.240
With Sissy Spritz, it's hair for the future, not the past.
01:30:26.240 --> 01:30:29.530
When you have great hair, people know you're a winner.
01:30:29.530 --> 01:30:34.030
Sissy Spritz may cause dry mouth, dilated pupils, paranoia, heart palpitations, and nosebleeds.
01:30:34.030 --> 01:30:35.130
But your hair will be great.
01:30:37.210 --> 01:30:40.290
This is K Chat.
01:30:40.290 --> 01:30:42.670
Welcome back to the show.
01:30:42.670 --> 01:30:50.830
I'm Amy Shekenhausen, and next up, we're going to be interviewing someone with a lot to say for herself, a woman who pretended to be a man and then wrote a book about it.
01:30:50.830 --> 01:30:53.810
I haven't read it, but I'm going to pretend I did.
01:30:53.810 --> 01:31:04.440
She's professor of anthro sociology and women's studies at the University of Vice City, and her name is Michaela Crapis, Crapidus.
01:31:04.440 --> 01:31:08.320
Michaela, Michaela, hi, welcome to K Chat.
01:31:08.320 --> 01:31:09.220
Hello.
01:31:09.220 --> 01:31:11.260
Hi.
01:31:11.260 --> 01:31:14.560
So, Michaela, you're a teacher.
01:31:14.560 --> 01:31:21.350
If you mean professor, yes, I have a doctorate, teachers are homely women who make minimum wage to keep the teenage boys off the streets during the day.
01:31:21.350 --> 01:31:25.720
I am very intelligent, and I'd rather talk about that.

01:31:30.000 --> 01:31:33.080
I'm trying to sell my book.
01:31:33.080 --> 01:31:36.580
Okay.
Now, it says here you wanted to be a man so much.
01:31:36.580 --> 01:31:38.820
You dressed up like one.
01:31:38.820 --> 01:31:41.130
Well, that's a load of crap, my dear.
01:31:41.130 --> 01:31:47.150
More misogynistic propaganda, I hate men, can't bear them.
01:31:47.150 --> 01:31:51.620
I think they're a complete waste of time and space, quite frankly, and a disaster for the planet.
01:31:51.620 --> 01:31:53.880
Me too, I just got dumped.
01:31:53.880 --> 01:31:55.970
Oh, well, it is unfortunate.
01:31:55.970 --> 01:32:00.450
You measure your self worth in relation to a man, my dear.
01:32:00.450 --> 01:32:03.040
Look at you, you could be an attractive girl.
01:32:03.040 --> 01:32:09.320
If you did some physical labor, cut your hair short, grew out your body hair, and wore boots, for example.
01:32:09.320 --> 01:32:12.930
You mustn't get sucked into their hetero patriarchy.
01:32:12.930 --> 01:32:15.970
But I like dating, having someone buy you dinner is great.
01:32:16.740 --> 01:32:22.860
Well, we'll come back to you and your problems, accepting who you really are.
01:32:22.860 --> 01:32:25.950
Let's talk about me a bit more.
01:32:25.950 --> 01:32:27.010
Okay.
01:32:27.010 --> 01:32:32.080
So, tell me about your book, you hate men a lot, and you dressed up like one.
01:32:32.080 --> 01:32:35.160
And now you've written a book about it, right?
01:32:35.940 --> 01:32:38.880
More or less, as I said, I'm very
01:32:38.880 --> 01:32:43.280
to understand, my dear, but I'll try to keep it simple.
01:32:43.280 --> 01:32:49.880
I've always been fascinated with the world of men, revolted, of course, but fascinated.
01:32:49.880 --> 01:32:54.800
Now, as an academic, I can get paid to write a book about pretty much anything.
01:32:54.800 --> 01:32:59.810
As long as I give it a complicated title, are you with me, gorgeous?
01:32:59.810 --> 01:33:01.540
Ooh, I think so.
01:33:01.540 --> 01:33:03.710
Good, then hold my hand, it helps me think.
01:33:03.710 --> 01:33:04.810
No.
01:33:04.810 --> 01:33:06.510
Okay, okay, sorry.
01:33:06.510 --> 01:33:08.430
Don't be so weird.
01:33:08.430 --> 01:33:12.580
God, everywhere I go, just like the university won't let me display my beautiful and sensual woodcuts.
01:33:12.580 --> 01:33:15.470
In the student comments, it makes me so angry.
01:33:16.170 --> 01:33:17.060
Where was I?

01:33:00.000 --> 01:33:03.000
You were talking about yourself?
01:33:03.000 --> 01:33:04.300
Oh, of course.
01:33:04.300 --> 01:33:10.050
The ego is a dangerous thing, especially in my case.
01:33:10.050 --> 01:33:12.230
I'm a Yuan.
01:33:12.230 --> 01:33:14.600
Anyway, so what I did was dress up like a man
01:33:14.600 --> 01:33:18.040
and enter into the man world.
01:33:18.040 --> 01:33:22.490
I can tell you it was more horrifying than I imagined.
01:33:22.990 --> 01:33:24.590
What did you do?
01:33:25.160 --> 01:33:29.880
Well, the first chapter, I was a roofer.
01:33:29.880 --> 01:33:36.130
These sexists spend all day on a roof talking about us, Amy.
